Douglas N. JACKSON, Jr., and Douglas N. Jackson, Jr. as Guardian ad Litem for Lisa Jackson, Paul Timothy Jackson and Malcolm Jackson, Minors, Appellants, v. Warren H. YOUNG and James Isherwood. No. 14112.

Before TUTTLE, Chief Judge, WISDOM, Circuit Judge, and JOHNSON, District Judge.

United States Court of Appeals , Third Circuit. Argued Dec. 14, 1962. Decided Jan. 3, 1963. Douglas N. Jackson, Jr., Stanford, Cal., argued pro se. James H. Isherwood, Christiansted, St. Croix, Virgin Islands (Warren H. Young, Young & Isherwood, Christiansted, St. Croix, V. I., on the brief), for appellees.

Before KALODNER and FORMAN, Circuit Judges, and ROSENBERG, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon review of the record we find no error. The Order of the District Court dated April 25, 1962 will be affirmed.
